records.addlTxt:
10:07 AM Defendant Dominick Allen Moore in court, in custody.  Attorney Fredric B. Anderson in court for Dominick Allen Moore.  Attorney Peter James Marvin Kruger in court for State of Wisconsin. Parties indicate an agreement. Defendant will plead to the sole count. 3 years prison sentence fashioned as 18 months initial confinement and 18 months extended supervision. Conditions of $50 fine plus costs. Sentence will run concurrent to other revoked file, Douglas County Case 20CF518. 
Defendant pleads guilty. Attorney Anderson stipulates to a factual basis. Court finds that the defendant's plea has been freely, intelligently, and voluntarily made. Court accepts the defendant's plea and finds the defendant guilty. 
Court orders a 3 year prison sentence fashioned as 1 year 6 months initial confinement and 1 year and 6 months extended supervision. 83 days sentence credit. Sentence will run concurrent to case 20CF518. Conditions of $50 fine plus costs, and programming as deemed appropriate by DOC. Defendant is eligible for both programs.
